sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1679006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a composite of RiboJ and I13504 which can be used to express GFP if added a promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to make other team easily use a GFP part to test the strength of a promoter, we constructed this part contain RiboJ before the BBa_I13504. Any team can use this part to measure the GFP expression if added a promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Qikai Qin

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1679038
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
After transcription, RiboJ becomes a section of functional RNA which comprises the sTRSV- ribozyme and an additional 23-nt hairpin immediately downstream to help expose the RBS. STRSV can cleaves the mRNA autocatalytically at a defined residue, which had the effect of cleaving extraneous RNA leaders that arose from transcription from promoters with different start sites.[1] Attributed to the biochemical function mentioned above, RiboJ has insulating capability. We use it to buffer synthetic circuits from genetic context.
[1] Lou C, Stanton B, Chen Y J, et al. Ribozyme-based insulator parts buffer synthetic circuits from genetic context[J]. Nature biotechnology, 2012, 30(11): 1137-1142.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: After transcription, RiboJ becomes a section of functional RNA which comprises the sTRSV- ribozyme and an additional 23-nt hairpin. Users can insert it into promoter and RBS to reduce noise caused by upstream sequence and stabilize mRNA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xihan Zhang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
